cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper focuses on Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks, specifically Word Sense Disambiguation (WSD), which falls under this category. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new supervised technique for transferring large pre-trained language model representations into a compressed representation, which involves machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with NLP tasks, which are a subset of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses contextual pretrained Language Models (LMs), which are based on neural networks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not directly deal with computer vision, the proposed technique for compressing language model representations could potentially be applied to image recognition tasks as well.
